sec.p:
The first cellularized ODE model in this work consists of the interactions of a population of cells and an extracellular virus using mass action. The virus infects uninfected cells U with an infection rate Î², which causes uninfected cells to join an infected cell population I1. Infected cells become virus-releasing cells I2 at a rate k, at which point they release unitless virus V at a rate p, modeling an eclipse phase. Virus-releasing cells die and join a dead cell population A at a rate d, modeling virally induced cell death. The virus decays at a rate c,
